      • printMailingLabels

        public java.lang.String printMailingLabels()
        Creates the To and From Labels for all the packages in the ArrayList
        Specified by:
        printMailingLabels in interface PackagesInterface
        Returns:
        a String with the To and From Labels of all packages in the ArrayList. Each label is separated by 2 blank lines Mailing Labels will be in the following format for each package in ArrayList:

        Labels

        (blank line)

        TO:(space)FirstName(space)LastName

        (spaces)StreetAddress

        (spaces)City(comma)(space)State(spaces)ZipCode

        (blank line)

        (blank line)

        Example:

        Labels

        (blank line)

        TO: John Smith

        22 Oak St.

        Gaithersburg, MD 20879

        (blank line)

        (blank line)

        FROM: Mable Marble

        45 Elm Ave.

        Somewhere, MN 55443

        (blank line)

        (blank line)

      • printDeliverySchedule

        public java.lang.String printDeliverySchedule()
        Creates a delivery Schedule for all packages in the ArrayList sorted by ZipCode of receiver of package
        Specified by:
        printDeliverySchedule in interface PackagesInterface
        Returns:
        a String with the all the Packages in the ArrayList sorted by ZipCode and displaying the first and last name of the receiver of the package

        Delivery schedule will be in the following format:

        Delivery Schedule

        (blank line)

        ZipCode(space)LastName(comma)(space)FirstName

        Example:

        Delivery Schedule

        (blank line)

        20874 Johnson, Bob

        20879 Smith, John
